CAREER STATISTICS

AT GEORGIA STATE: Played one season at GSU (2023) as a graduate transfer safety from Lehigh.

2023: Graduate transfer who earned a starting role at safety ...Fourth on the team with 71 tackles, including seven tackles for loss, one interception and six pass breakups ... Season-high 12 tackles with 1.5 TFL and a pass breakup to help hold Charlotte to 58 yards rushing ... Added 11 tackles in win at Coastal Carolina ... Grabbed his first interception at GSU vs. Troy ... Made seven tackles with two TFL in win over Marshall ... Two pass breakups in win at Louisiana as the GSU defense allowed just 289 total yards ... Broke up a pass in bowl game win over Utah State.

BEFORE GSU: Three-time, first-team All-Patriot League selection at Lehigh ... Made 198 career tackles, including 21 tackles for loss, with two interceptions in 36 games ... Named first-team All-Patriot League for the third straight year in 2022, when he had 78 tackles, 11.5 TFL and one interception ... Selected Patriot League Defensive Player of the Week after setting career highs with 14 tackles and three tackles for loss at Georgetown ... As a junior he led the squad with eight pass breakups and tied for the team lead with 69 tackles ... As a freshman, he was named Patriot League Special Teams Player of the Week after blocking a punt versus Merrimack.

HIGH SCHOOL: First-team all-state selection at Malvern Prep ... Two-time first-team all-league and all-area … First-team All-Philadelphia and All-Southeastern Pa.… Also competed in basketball and track and field.
